This category of Technologys describes a wide range of measures and strategies aimed at ensuring the safety, preparedness, and response in the face of emergencies, crises, and contagious diseases. This includes the use of personal protective equipment (PPE), safety protocols, emergency response planning, quarantine facilities, risk detection systems, safety monitoring systems, and safety regulations. It also encompasses the development of emergency preparedness plans, crisis management protocols, and resilient-based practices. Additionally, this category addresses the importance of risk assessment and management, early warning systems, and risk communication strategies to increase awareness and educate about transmission risks. The goal is to create safe and social spaces, protect individuals with high-risk factors, and promote the use of technology, materials, and systems that are resilient to emergencies. This category also highlights workplace safety technology, stress management techniques, and health and safety executive (HSE) measures to enhance overall safety and well-being.